docs.abstract: The idea that Black Lives Matter, woke culture and the #MeToo movement have gone too far has propelled a backlash across the political spectrum.
docs.snippet: The idea that Black Lives Matter, woke culture and the #MeToo movement have gone too far has propelled a backlash across the political spectrum.
docs.lead_paragraph: “TooFar” is not a viral hashtag — yet — but it is the prevailing ethos of the moment, the sentiment animating our politics and our culture, the sense that is propelling a massive backlash across the political spectrum.

docs.abstract: The artist Desmond Lewis brings the glow of professional fireworks to under-resourced communities in the South.
docs.snippet: The artist Desmond Lewis brings the glow of professional fireworks to under-resourced communities in the South.
docs.lead_paragraph: GREENWOOD, Miss. — On Saturday night, June 18, the Memphis-based artist Desmond Lewis was in a public park unloading cakes — bundles of fireworks connected by a high-speed fuse — from a pickup truck. On the other side of a nearby tree line waited about 150 expectant onlookers for the Juneteenth celebration in the city that is heralded as “the cotton capital of the world.”

docs.abstract: “Picture the Dream,” on display at the New-York Historical Society, shows that children, far from being mere witnesses to the civil rights movement, have played central roles in it.
docs.snippet: “Picture the Dream,” on display at the New-York Historical Society, shows that children, far from being mere witnesses to the civil rights movement, have played central roles in it.
docs.lead_paragraph: In a verdant rural setting, a weathered gray fence separates two girls, one Black, one white. The Black child extends her hand as the white girl, already straddling the fence’s top rail, reaches down. Although they barely grasp each other’s fingers, a viewer can sense their curiosity, their anticipation, their desire to surmount this barrier.

headline.main: Viewing the Civil Rights Movement Through Children’s Books
headline.print_headline: Civil Rights Movement  Through Children’s Books
